    "narrative": "The priority for Ghost Ride the WHIP today centers on the elite speed-opportunity nexus, headlined by **Corbin Carroll**, whose 79.74 score makes him our clear lineup anchor against Pop. With a favorable wind and an advantageous matchup, **Corbin Carroll** is primed to exploit the battery, though we\u2019ve docked his projection slightly to account for the catcher\u2019s elite pop time. Following closely is **Trevor Story** (69.04), who benefits significantly from Pallante\u2019s slow delivery, creating a high-upside environment for stolen bases. **Josh Naylor** (68.46) also projects as a top-tier play, as his power profile aligns perfectly with the exploitable xERA of Bolton, making him the engine of our utility production for the afternoon.\n\nWe are navigating a few volatile situations, most notably with **Mickey Moniak**, whose strong 65.20 score is currently threatened by a 39% rain risk; if the skies open, his production will plummet despite a favorable platoon advantage. On the bench, **Zach McKinstry** came the closest to cracking the starting nine with a 50.08 efficiency rating. While his ability to run on the basepaths is elite, he was ultimately displaced by the higher raw projected output of **James Wood** and **Seiya Suzuki**. While **Jose Caballero** remains an intriguing speed asset, his poor projected batting position and negative platoon splits kept him comfortably below our 40-point threshold, preserving our game caps for more efficient matchups.",
